data-triple-N3.o: "Pashtun people (Pashto: Paxtan; also spelled Pushtun, Pakhtun or Pukhtun), also known as ethnic Afghans or Pathans, are an Iranic ethnic group belonging to Afghanistan and Pakistan. They are typically characterised by the usage of the Eastern Iranian Pashto language and practice of Pashtunwali, which is a traditional set of ethics guiding individual and communal conduct."@en
